\begin_layout Standard
The canonical definition of a graph is that of two sets: a set 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

 of vertices and a set 
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

 of edges.
 An edge 
\begin_inset Formula $e_{k}\in E$
\end_inset

