 of the same type.
 Conventional tensors do not have any corresponding notion of multi-sexual
 connectors, as described above.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The similarity btween tensors and jigsaw pieces is ultimately anchored on
 just one commonality: it takes two, and exactly two connectors, to connect
 and form a link.
 One cannot form a link from zero, onje, three or more connectors.
 Likewise, tensor indexes contract by pairs: once cannot contract three
 or more indexes together.
 There is no loss of generality from this restriction; one emulates multi-index
 contraction by using diagonal tensors: those whose entries are zero everywhere
 except on the diagonal.
 Likewise for the jigsaw conception: if one wishes to connect together three
 (or more) connectors into one unit, one creates (without loss of generality)
 a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

